\pard\nowidctlpar\lang2057\b\f1 Summary of the previous fms:\b0\par
\par
\b Part 1 - L'Arsene\b0 : The story begins with Garrett arriving to a distant unknown town. Everything our thief needs at the time is to get some rest in a comfortable hostel.\par
But isn\rquote t he shocked when he wakes up to find out all his goods have disappeared! Garrett must accept the fact, someone has robbed him!\par
The larceny was signed by someone called L'Arsene who, as Garrett will later find out, is the local master thief and who is accompanied by solid group of tough brigands.\par
Garrett will chase after L'Arsene in a confrontation that can only end with the fall of L'Arsene.\par
\par
\b Part 2 - Emilie Victor\b0 : Garrett inadvertently finds himself in the manor of no other than Sir Deloret, tyrannical and despotic lord of the corrupted town.\par
Garrett will meet a strange person, Emilie, who will grant him a very useful key for his following mission.\par
\par
\b Part 3 - The Korrigans\b0 : L'Arsene has escaped from prison. This town is definitely too dangerous for Garrett and he\rquote s had enough of it. He\rquote s resolved to leave but bad luck seems to pursue him. The town is under quarantine due to the invasion of mysterious evil creatures commonly known as "Korrigans".\par
Right now a ship is moored at the harbour, ready to set sail in a few hours. But all the accesses to the town are closely watched by the town militia, which has been reinforced due to the psychosis created by the apparition of the Korrigans.\par
Time presses and Garrett cannot see a way to get into the ship and leave town. But then he receives a message by no other that L\rquote Arsene\rquote s sister, Berenice. And she proposes a strange deal.\lang1036\b\f0\par
\pard\b0 ________________________________________________________________________________\par
\b\par
Part 4 - The Den \b0\par
\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\lang2057\f1 When Garrett regains consciousness, beaten up by L\rquote Arsene\rquote s thugs, he finds out that he is locked up in a dark and stinking cell. He can hear the moans of other prisoners around him.\par
Raising his eyes he can make out on the opposite side of the bars a familiar proudly-smiling shape: L'Arsene. His implacable enemy. He seems to have been watching him sleep for some time. Beside him, a hooded man stands, La Bourrique undoubtedly, L'Arsene\rquote s faithful lieutenant.\par
They have both been waiting for their prisoner to wake up, to impose their humiliating victory on him.\par
\par
Garrett suffers, he\rquote s been derided, and he is hungry, and all that makes him very angry.\par
First thing to do, escape this stinking prison and try to find something to eat.\par
Then it will all be between L\rquote Arsene and him.\lang1036\f0\par
